div.p:
And I say that this is to be seen on both sides, when a man subdues himself on the right side and when he gives an opportunity to the left one. But the mind that has learnt to see discriminately, is able to observe how compulsion on both sides dominates freedom, when the force which is not from nature, is born
from the submission of the will. I do not mean the usual force,
which is very difficult; but that which is called secondary.
